  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral Humanitarian Assistance for Displaced and Mobile Populations in Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to contribute towards efforts to address urgent humanitarian needs through a multi-sectoral approach focused on providing integrated support to displaced and vulnerable crisis-affected populations. To achieve this aim, the project will focus on three inter-related outcomes centered on i) collecting and sharing with partners&#x2019; up-to-date information needed to respond effectively to humanitarian needs; ii) providing emergency shelter and non-food items to vulnerable populations; and, iii) mitigating potential causes of tension and conflict (resource-driven and inter-community) by promoting peaceful co-existence through improved access to basic services and livelihood opportunities. As the recent outbreak of COVID-19 is further exacerbating an already stretched health system and worsening an already dire economic situation, the project will include mainstreamed and dedicated activities to respond to the COVID-19 outbreak in particular with regards to health and livelihoods but also water, sanitation and hygiene activities.</narrative>
  </description>
